'''Jerry Harte''' ([[April 20]], [[1930s#1931|1931]]&ndash;[[February]] [[2018]]) was an [[Wikipedia:Americans|American]] actor, director, and musician who appeared in the [[1980]] film [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']]. He is credited as "Head Controller" in the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel Forces]].

==Biography==
Harte has been married to [[Wikipedia:English people|English]] actress [[Wikipedia:Julia McKenzie|Julia McKenzie]] since [[1971]].<ref name="Telegraph">{{WebCite|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/6086837/Julia-McKenzie-on-being-the-new-Miss-Marple-interview.html|text=Julia McKenzie on being the new Miss Marple: interview|author=Patay, Ajesh|date=2009-08-25, 5:35 PM BST|work=[http://www.telegraph.co.uk The Telegraph]|quote=With a holiday booked for February and still no news, McKenzie jetted off to New Zealand with her American actor-director husband of 37 years Jerry Harte.|archivedate=20180709115634}}</ref><ref name="Daily Mail">{{WebCite|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2942353/I-m-thrilled-mother-law-hell-Julia-McKenzie-s-TV-version-JK-Rowling-s-Casual-Vacancy-time-s-villain.html|text='I'm thrilled to be the mother-in-law from hell!' Julia McKenzie's back in the TV version of JK Rowling's The Casual Vacancy and this time she's the villain|author=Johnston, Jenny|date=2015-02-06, 17:31 EST|work=[http://www.dailymail.co.uk/ushome/index.html Daily Mail Online]|quote=Her husband, the American actor and musician Jerry Harte [&hellip;]|archivedate=20160102123717}}</ref>

===''The Empire Strikes Back''===
The [[Star Wars Insider 74|''Star Wars Insider'' 74]] article ''[[Who's Who in Echo Base]]'', written by [[Josh Radke]], incorrectly states that Jerry Harte played [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] [[Controller/Legends|controller]] [[Romas Navander/Legends|Romas Navander]], a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] character, in ''The Empire Strikes Back''. In fact, the Navander role was portrayed by actor [[Burnell Tucker]], while Harte played [[Unidentified Rebel major|another Echo Base officer]] who was not named in ''[[Star Wars]]'' Legends.<ref name="Actor">This assertion is based on a visual comparison of actors Jerry Harte and [[Burnell Tucker]], using pictures of both men in their respective various acting roles (see: [http://www.aveleyman.com/ActorCredit.aspx?ActorID=37407 Jerry Harte] and [http://www.aveleyman.com/ActorCredit.aspx?ActorID=24795 Burnell Tucker]). Comparing both actors demonstrates that Tucker played [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] [[Controller/Legends|controllers]] [[Romas Navander/Legends|Romas Navander]] and [[Wyron Serper/Legends|Wyron Serper]] in [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']], while Harte played an [[Unidentified Rebel major|unnamed Rebel officer]]. Therefore, the claim from the [[Star Wars Insider 74|''Star Wars Insider'' 74]] article ''[[Who's Who in Echo Base]]'' that Harte played Navander is incorrect.</ref>

